<section id="writingtask1">


<p class="popuptext"> You should spend about 40 minutes on this task.</p>
<p class="popuptext"><b> Present a written argument or case to an educated reader with no specialist knowledge of the following topic.</b></p>
<p class="popuptext"><b> Rapid progress in the fields of genetics and gene therapy are likely to have profound effects on people's live in the foreseeable future. By altering people's genetic make-up, it may be possible for doctors to cure hereditary diseases, and for parents to choose important characteristic for their children such as their sex or level of intelligence. Such a development would be a major breakthrough for humanity and would solve many present-day problems.</b></p>
<p class="popuptext"><b> To what extent do you agree or disagree?</b></p>
<p class="popuptext">You should write at least 250 words.</p>
<p class="popuptext">You should use your own ideas, knowledge and experience and support your arguments with examples and relevant evidence.</p>

		</section>
<section id="fb1">
  <p class="feedbacktext">1. Parents could make sure their children were intelligent.</p>
</section>

<section id="fb2">
   <p class="feedbacktext">2. Criminals could be 'cured' of their criminal tendencies.</p>
</section>

<section id="fb3">
   <p class="feedbacktext">3. Could upset natural balances such as the male to female ratio.</p>
</section>

<section id="fb4">
   <p class="feedbacktext">4. Fatal diseases could be cured.</p>
</section>

<section id="fb5">
   <p class="feedbacktext">5. Could be controlled by political regimes.</p>
</section>

<section id="fb6">
   <p class="feedbacktext">6. Children and future generations will not be able to give their consent to genetic changes.</p>
</section>

<section id="fb7">
